Twitter App PART 1 Steps:

- Create new rails app 'twitter'
- Run server, verify working
- Scaffold User { handle:string }
- Migrate
- Add a user { @daretorant }
- Migrate
- Scaffold Tweet { body:string, handle:string }
- Add a few tweets with handle @daretorant
- Change twitter handle of user 1 to @daretotalk
- Notice that tweets don't change
- Add a migration to add user_id:integer to tweets
- (SLIDE: Explain Migrations at a high level)
- Existing migrations! Review them
- Fill in migration
- Run migration
- Turns out no change to view! What the heck... we need to edit the view to modify Edit page.
- Update Edit view to show user_id, set user_id to 1 on tweet
- Remove the handle column
- Link the twitter handle
- Link URLs inside the tweet
- Add a URL to profile photo for User
- do some CSS tweaks
- Git init
- Create GitHub repository
- Push to github